      q: "Where should you eat in Mystic?",
      a: "For dinner: The Oyster Club (seasonal, coastal, reserve 2-3 weeks ahead), Engine Room (locals' favorite), or Bravo Bravo (upscale Italian). For lunch: S&P Oyster Restaurant on the water. For coffee or pastries: Sift Bake Shop, a James Beard semifinalist. Avoid Mystic Pizza if food quality matters more than the movie nostalgia.",
    },
    {
      q: "How much time do you need in Mystic?",
      a: "A full day (8-10 hours) is right for most visitors. You can do a half-day if you're picking just one attraction (Aquarium or Seaport), but the value of the trip multiplies if you include both plus a downtown meal. Mystic also works as a 2-day stay with an overnight, particularly if you want to dine at the Oyster Club without rushing back.",
    },
    {
      q: "Is Mystic, CT open year-round?",
      a: "Yes. Mystic Aquarium and Mystic Seaport both operate year-round, with reduced winter hours. Downtown restaurants and shops mostly stay open year-round as well, with some reduced winter schedules. Mystic is one of the better off-season day trips from Watch Hill since most of the village's offerings are weather-independent.",
    },
